Hernando Rivera Cervantes captured the lightning strikes inside the ash cloud of the Colima volcano in Mexico as it erupted . 
  The volcano is one of the most active in Mexico and has been warned to prepare for an evacuation . 
  The photographer spent eight hours waiting to capture the images of the volcano . 
  Lightning is thought to occur in volcanic ash clouds due to the build up of electric charge in the cloud . 
